<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-47-0672 </DOCNO><TEXT>The need to equip conventional coal-fired power stations with flue-gasdesulphurisation and nitrogen-removal plants has been the motivationfor developing alternative solutions which will increase efficiency levelsand improve existing emission and waste-processing systems. The technicaloptions available include atmospheric and, more particularly, circulatingfluidised-bed combustors, pressurised fluidised-bed combustors and gas-steamturbine combined-cycle power stations with integral coal gasification.5 refs., 1 fig., 4 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>